</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MITSUAKI IWAGO'S KANGAROOS by Mitsuaki Iwago (Chronicle: $19.95; unpaginated). 
The only large animal that uses hopping as a means of locomotion, kangaroos 
resemble a malformed cross between a human and a rabbit.The noted Japanese 
wildlife photographer made several trips to Australia to document the red 
kangaroo, one of the larger species. Although most of these dramatic pictures 
appear to have been chosen for aesthetic qualities, rather than scientific 
content, they reveal the shifting moods of these oddly appealing marsupials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
