<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MY WEEDS: A Gardener's Botany by Sara Stein (Houghton Mifflin: $11.95; 229 
pp., illustrated). The author of several gardening books, Stein notes wryly 
that gardens produce more weeds than anything else: "Weeds coerce my attention 
as tenaciously as a toddler hanging on my knees. They raise all kinds of 
questions, not the least of which is what are they doing in my garden in the 
first place." She explains how the weeds got into her garden in her 
entertaining accounts of common North American plant pests. Interweaving facts 
with stories about her own garden, Stein offers a tongue-in-cheek account that 
will strike a responsive chord in any frustrated gardener. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Book Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
