<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'DIABOLIQUE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Wilmington 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Henri-Georges Clouzot's famous 1955 French shocker mixes perverse psychology, 
a middle-class triangle and a murder scheme in a Balzacian milieu with 
supernatural overtones. Loaded with wicked insights and nasty thrills, it's 
been copied repeatedly ever since its release -- and is about to be remade by 
Hollywood. With Vera Clouzot and Simone Signoret (pictured from left) and Paul 
Meurisse (Bravo Saturday at 8 p.m., next Sunday at midnight). 
</P>
<P>
 Other four-star films airing this week: 
</P>
<P>
 Red River TNT, Sunday, 7:15 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Killers (1946 version) A&E, Tuesday, 1 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Major Barbara Bravo, Tuesday, 2:30 and 9:35 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosemary's Baby Bravo, Wednesday, 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 To Kill a Mockingbird A&E, Saturday, 5 and 9 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Julia Disney Channel, Saturday, 5 p.m. Michael Wilmington 
</P>
