<P>
 Roxette, "Crash! Boom! Bang!,"(***) EMI. As they've done with ABBA and the 
Carpenters, rock music's intelligentsia 10 years from now are sure to embrace 
this impossibly un-hip Swedish pair and their kicky melodies, sublimely silly 
lyrics, stinging guitar and bald teen appeal.On their fourth album, Per Gessle 
and Marie Fredriksson have evolved not a whit, turning out more deliciously 
overwrought ballads, bubblegum and great almost-grunge. 
