<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUE CONCERN SHOULD BE REDUCING NICOTINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Will the new product ("R.J. Reynolds to Introduce a Less-Smelly Cigarette," 
Oct. 11) be a new version of its Salem menthol brand featuring a cigarette 
paper that reduces stale odors? Apparently there is still no concern with 
reducing the manipulation of the nicotine content. We can now look forward to 
cases of the sweetest-smelling nicotine-infected cancerous lungs in history. 
</P>
<P>
 However, if R.J. Reynolds really wanted to provide an example of good 
citizenship, it could help stamp out the country's vicarious smoking habit by 
treating its product with substances that decrease the cigarettes' nicotine 
content while at the same time increasing its stale and obnoxious odors. 
</P>
<P>
 LOUIS ROLMI 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 
</P>
</TEXT>
