<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: CHUNNEL FARES ANNOUNCED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reservations for Eurostar, the high-speed passenger train service from London 
to Paris and Brussels via the English Channel tunnel, open Monday at prices 
that were finally released last week along with yet another start date for the 
service -- Nov. 14. 
</P>
<P>
 One-way fares for the 3-hour ride through the Chunnel will range $75-$154 
during the so-called "Discovery" period from Nov. 14 to Jan. 21.One-way 
"Discovery Special" rates are $75 per person for non-refundable, 
non-transferable tickets purchased 14 days in advance. Second-class "Discovery 
Standard" seats, which carry no restrictions, cost $123; first-class "Discovery 
Gold" fares, which include a meal, are $154. 
</P>
<P>
 Initially there will be only two round trips a day, Monday to Friday. The 
tunnel will continue to be closed on Saturday for engineering work. Passengers 
will, however, be able to travel on Sunday evenings, offering the prospect of a 
long weekend in any of the three cities. Reservations and information are 
available from Rail Europe (800) EUROSTAR or BritRail (800) 677-8585. 
</P>
</TEXT>
