<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: MORE TERRA-COTTA WARRIORS IN CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The last of three pits of terra-cotta warriors and horses near China's ancient 
capital of Xian has been opened to the public.The cave is believed to contain 
more than 1,400 pottery figures and chariots, including more than 100 warriors 
on horseback. Excavation began in March and is expected to continue for about 
five years, the official Xinhua News Agency reported. The warriors were 
discovered 20 years ago by peasants who were sinking wells. Since then, about 
26 million people have visited the excavation site. 
</P>
