<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Susan Bliss 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TCHAIKOVSKY: BARRY DOUGLAS, piano, London Symphony, Philharmonia Orchestra, 
Leonard Slatkin, conductor for -- Piano Concerto No. 1; Concert Fantasy. RCA 
Victor Red Seal 09026 61632-2.Piano Concerto No. 2; Piano Concerto No. 3. RCA 
Victor Red Seal 09026 61633-2. These two discs, issued separately, comprise 
handsome reminders of the qualities that made Douglas the first Western winner 
of the Tchaikovsky Competition since 1958. Each work is given a powerful and 
stylish performance -- technically impressive and remarkably refined. 
Pristinely partnered by the London Symphony, the Belfast-born pianist recorded 
-- and RCA originally released -- the First Concerto in 1986, the year he took 
the gold, in Moscow. The other, less familiar offerings -- all in collaboration 
with the Philharmonia -- followed in 1991 and 1992. The forces maintain a 
unanimity in their approach -- personable, moving, flashy, eminently romantic, 
but never descending into bombast. Susan Bliss 
</P>
</TEXT>
