<TEXT>
<P>
 MORE PEARLS: Some passages in the "Vitalogy" book used by Pearl Jam in its 
album packaging may draw extra attention. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's a combination of things that are funny and maybe some things that 
were ahead of their time -- including one thing from the old book saying that 
the biggest cause of death for healthy young men is 'self-pollution,' " says 
Beck. 
</P>
<P>
 A reference to fellow Seattle-rocker Kurt Cobain's drug use and suicide, which 
had a deep effect on Pearl Jam?  
</P>
<P>
 Curtis refuses to speculate on whether such elements have any "hidden" 
meanings and adds that none of the songs on the album are to his knowledge 
specifically about Cobain.  
</P>
<P>
 Curtis does say that there are hopes for a concert tour after New Year's, 
though no replacement has been chosen for fired drummer Dave Abruzzede. Steve 
Hochman 
</P>
