<HEADLINE>
<P>
DNA TESTS EXONERATE MAN AFTER 10 YEARS IN PRISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. George Allen Friday freed a man who served nearly 10 years in prison for 
a rape that DNA tests show he did not commit. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have proceeded with great care and caution," Allen said at a news 
conference announcing that Edward Honaker was being released. "I'm satisfied 
today that I've made the right decision." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102394-0125 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 091325 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
