<HEADLINE>
<P>
INTRODUCING THE CHUTZPAH AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I suggest that The Times institute a Chutzpah Award to be given on a regular 
basis to that public figure who makes the most egregiously outrageous and 
illogical comment on a matter of public interest during the period under 
review. As initial recipients of this award I nominate these individuals: 
</P>
<P>
 * Dist. Atty.Michael R. Capizzi: After his office bungled the case of the 
supposed Laguna Canyon arsonist, he had the gall to attempt to shift the blame 
onto the media!  
</P>
<P>
 * The Rev. Lou Sheldon: He justified his support for Proposition 187 on the 
grounds that illegal immigrants are not mentioned in the Bible. What arrant 
nonsense! Did Jesus check the nationality of those upon whom He worked his 
miracles? Did the good Samaritan ask for a green card before he helped the 
wounded traveler?  
</P>
<P>
 From his past comments we know of Sheldon's virulent antipathy toward 
homosexuals and abortionists, and now he has added illegals to his verboten 
list.  
</P>
<P>
 W.A. JONES 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 
