<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP; GUSTIN LEADS WYOMING OVER AZTECS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Gustin passed for five touchdowns and 401 yards to lead Wyoming to a 
52-35 victory over San Diego State Saturday in a Western Athletic Conference 
game at Laramie, Wyo. 
</P>
<P>
 Gustin completed 31 of 42 passes, including touchdown passes of four, five, 
25, 38 and 42 yards to lead the Cowboys (4-4, 2-2), who held only a 24-21 lead 
at halftime. The 38-yard touchdown pass to Brent Tillman was one of his 15 
catches, breaking the school record of 13 set in 1992 by Ryan Yarborough. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Christopherson, who caught Gustin's four-yard touchdown pass, rushed for 
152 yards to increase his season total to 1,026, making him only the second 
Cowboy to have two consecutive seasons of 1,000 yards or more. The first was 
Dabby Dawson in 1988 and 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego State fell to 3-5, 1-5. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jake Campbell scored three touchdowns, two in a 21-point third quarter, and 
Air Force (4-3, 3-2) scored a 42-7 WAC victory over Fresno State (4-4, 2-2) at 
Air Force Academy, Colo. . . . John Walsh threw three touchdown passes as No. 
21 Brigham Young (7-1, 5-1) used a balanced offense to hold off Texas El Paso 
(3-5, 1-4) at El Paso, 34-28. Walsh completed 26 of 39 passes for 330 yards and 
Jamal Willis ran for 136 yards and a touchdown in 19 carries. . . . Stoney Case 
ran for two touchdowns, passed for another and became the first major-college 
player in NCAA history to throw for more than 8,000 yards and run for more than 
1,000 as New Mexico (2-6) won, 56-31, over New Mexico State (2-6) in a 
nonconference game at Las Cruces, N.M. Case, who scored his 26th career rushing 
touchdown, was 18 of 25 for 267 yards and rushed for another 49 yards. EAST 
</P>
<P>
 Pennsylvania (5-0, 3-0) scored all its points in the first half in a 24-0 Ivy 
League victory over Brown (3-3, 0-3) at Providence. Terrance Stokes, who 
carried 22 times for 97 yards, scored two touchdowns for Penn, which won its 
17th game in a row, the longest current streak in Division I-AA. . . . Aaron 
Berryman caught a 14-yard touchdown pass from Per Larson with 49 seconds 
remaining as Cornell (6-0, 3-0) rallied for a 17-14 Ivy League victory over 
Dartmouth (3-3, 1-2) at Ithaca, N.Y. Cornell's Chad Levitt rushed for 172 yards 
in 32 carries, his fourth consecutive 100-yard game. . . . Freshman Tom Ludwig 
had three interceptions as Princeton (5-1, 2-1) won its fifth in a row with an 
18-7 victory over error-plagued Harvard (3-3, 1-2) in an Ivy League game at 
Princeton, N.J. . . . Jamie Schwalde completed 20 of 28 passes for 265 yards, 
giving Columbia (3-2-1, 1-2) a 30-9 victory over Yale (3-3, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Kurt Heiss kicked a 24-yard field goal with no time remaining as Army (3-4) 
won its second consecutive one-point game, recording a 25-21 victory over The 
Citadel (3-4) at West Point, N.Y. . . . Marty Lowe completed 29 of 36 passes 
for 264 yards and Anthony Shelman scored two touchdowns in the decisive third 
quarter as Louisville (4-3), bouncing back from last week's upset loss to Army, 
pulled away to a 35-14 victory over Navy (1-6) at Annapolis, Md. BIG WEST 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Maxwell threw for four touchdowns and ran for a score as Nevada (7-1, 
4-0) rolled to a 42-10 Big West victory over San Jose State (1-6, 1-1) at San 
Jose. . . . Junior Joe Abdullah carried 36 times for 272 yards, caught nine 
passes for 52 yards and scored three touchdowns as Pacific (4-3, 2-1) recorded 
a 30-16 Big West victory over Arkansas State (1-7, 0-4) at Jonesboro, Ark. . . 
. Fullback Kenyon Cotton ran for 146 yards and a touchdown to lead Southwestern 
Louisiana (4-4, 4-1) to a 27-25 Big West victory over Utah State (2-5, 1-2) at 
Logan, Utah. 
</P>
