<P>
MISSISSIPPI ST. SCORES 66, TAITE SETS PASSING MARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Derrick Taite threw for a school-record 466 yards and four touchdowns as 
Mississippi State routed Tulane, 66-22, Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Taite threw to Chris Jones for a 20-yard touchdown pass three minutes into the 
game, and added first-half scores on throws of 60 yards to Shaston Coleman, 47 
yards to Bernard Euell and 48 yards to Eric Moulds, who had five catches for 
160 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Taite was 21 of 30 in breaking the record of 429 yards by Dave Marler set in 
1978. His four touchdowns tie a record held by Tony Shell. 
</P>
<P>
 Mississippi State (5-2) outgained Tulane (1-6), 554-286, and reached 60 points 
for the first time since 1946. 
