<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL ROUNDUP; LONGSHOT POST IT WINS KEENELAND'S ALCIBIADES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Longshot Post It won the $107,500 Alcibiades Stakes at Keeneland by two 
lengths Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Post It won the 1 1/16-mile race for 2-year-old fillies in 1:46 1/5 and paid 
$26, $7.80 and $18.20.Morris Code returned $7.40 and $12, while Cat Appeal paid 
$9. 
</P>
<P>
 More than $135,000 of the $165,000 wagered to show in the race was bet on 3-10 
favorite Lilly Capote, who finished fourth, resulting in the unusually high 
show payoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Serious Spender beat odds-on favorite Unaccounted For by a head to win the 
$100,000 Discovery Handicap at Aqueduct. 
</P>
<P>
 Serious Spender covered 1 1/8 miles in a slow 1:51 1/5 and returned $12.20 and 
$2.90. Unaccounted For paid $2.20. There was no show wagering. 
</P>
