<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; PEPPERDINE HOLDS OFF THE ANTEATERS FOR WATER POLO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pepperdine goalie Vatche Shirikjian blocked Peter Muller's shot with three 
seconds left as sixth-ranked Pepperdine held on to defeat UC Irvine, 11-10, in 
a Mountain Pacific Sports Federation water polo game Saturday at Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters (5-11, 1-6) led Pepperdine, 9-8, entering the fourth quarter, 
but the Waves' Jack Kocur scored two goals, including the winner with 19 
seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Kocur's goal early in the quarter tied the score, 9-9. Twenty-four seconds 
later, Irvine's Omar Amr scored, but Pepperdine's Alan Herrmann tied it, 10-10, 
with 3 minutes 23 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Muller led the Anteaters with three goals. Ryan Bailey, Ofer Horn and 
Matt Maunz added two goals each. 
</P>
<P>
 Herrmann led Pepperdine (10-4, 5-1) with four goals. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa Pacific 4, Southern California College 2 -- Sam Nocura and Hector Perez 
each scored for Southern California College (5-8-1, 1-5). Matt Johnston scored 
three goals for Azusa Pacific (11-4-2, 5-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Biola 4, Concordia 1 -- Joel Dietrich scored Concordia's only goal. Concordia 
dropped to 4-10-1 (0-6 in conference). 
</P>
<P>
 Ziggy Trevor scored once for Biola (4-2 in conference). 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Nevada 3, UC Irvine 0 -- Tiffany Nuemeier had 20 kills to lead Nevada (8-14, 
4-9). Kelly Martin also had 16 kills and Monica Petrilli had 46 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Popi Edwards had 25 kills for UC Irvine (5-15, 4-9). 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa Pacific 3, Concordia 0 -- Stephanie Benitez had nine kills to lead Azusa 
Pacific, 15-8, 15-6, 16-14. Azusa Pacific improved to 18-7, 9-2 in conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennifer Guzman had 12 kills for Concordia (12-13, 2-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 3, Southern California College 2 -- Genevieve Wright had 22 
kills and Celeste Young added 19 for host SCC (16-8, 5-6), which lost, 5-15, 
7-15, 15-13, 15-8, 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Tracy Ainger had 20 kills and Alyson Wilson added 14 for Fresno Pacific (18-7, 
8-3), ranked 12th in NAIA Division I. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second time in as many nights that SCC lost a match after winning 
the first two games. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Dominguez Hills 3, Chapman 1 -- Shawna Parkinson had 19 kills for 
visiting Chapman (20-7), which lost, 15-10, 15-11, 13-15, 15-5. Jennifer Clark 
had 20 kills for Dominguez Hills (5-26). 
</P>
<P>
 Christi Park had 37 assists for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Cal Poly Pomona Bronco Cross-Country Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State's Bendzick fifth -- Pat Bendzick finished in 25:32.8 in the 
men's race for Long Beach. His teammate, Dennis Swaningson, was sixth in 25:41. 
UC Irvine's Todd Couleton was eighth in 25:45, and Southern California 
College's Jason Schaefer was ninth in 25:52. 
</P>
<P>
 In the women's race, Sonya Berro of Long Beach State was 11th in 18:51, and 
Tiffany York of Irvine was 13th in 18:54. 
</P>
