<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRENTWOOD FOILS FAITH BAPTIST IN BATTLE OF UNBEATENS, 34-18 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES CHESNUTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a matchup between unbeaten teams, Scott Fagan rushed for 96 yards in 19 
carries, including touchdowns of two and 42 yards, to help lead host Brentwood 
to an easy 34-18 Delphic League victory over Faith Baptist Saturday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Brentwood (7-0, 2-0) put the game out of reach in the second quarter, as Fagan 
contributed his second touchdown, and running back Rico Saken chipped in two 
more scores within less than 6 1/2 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Saken finished with 95 yards in four carries. His touchdown runs were of 54 
and 32 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist (6-1, 1-1) scored with seven seconds remaining in the third 
quarter on a 44-yard run by back Rani Zahr. 
</P>
<P>
 Zahr finished with 16 carries for 122 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist quarterback Judd Granzow completed seven of 19 passes for 59 
yards, including a 26-yard touchdown to Tywane Patterson. 
</P>
<P>
 The Contenders' other score was by safety Robert Escalante, who returned an 
interception 35 yards with 10:24 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Brentwood quarterback Chris Malcolm scored on a 19-yard run, and kicker Phil 
Fagan was four-for four on extra-point attempts. JAMES CHESNUTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
