<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESERT THWARTS ANTELOPE VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY PRICE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bongkuk Pak's 18-yard touchdown pass to Danny Quinal with 46 seconds remaining 
and Xavier Acosta's conversion kick propelled College of the Desert to a 21-20 
Foothill Conference victory over Antelope Valley on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 If Antelope Valley could find any consolation, it was in an offense that put 
together sustained scoring drives. The Antelopes (1-6, 1-4 in conference play), 
who had only two scoring drives of any length all season, marched 76, 80 and 55 
yards for touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley took a 20-7 lead through three quarters on a 13-yard pass from 
Mike Gleich to Chris Brown and one-yard runs by Roosevelt Miller and Domino 
Gibson. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller led all rushers with 129 yards in 21 carries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
