<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; L.A. BAPTIST SNEAKS PAST MARANATHA, 7-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Adrian Kaali-Nagy's 29-yard touchdown reception and subsequent conversion kick 
midway through the fourth quarter lifted L.A. Baptist High to a 7-6 victory 
over Maranatha in an Alpha League game Saturday night at San Marino High. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior running back Surfy Taylor, who rushed for 237 yards in 31 carries, gave 
Maranatha a 6-0 lead on a four-yard run early in the second quarter. Taylor, 
also a defensive back, had 14 tackles and forced a fumble that the Minutemen 
recovered. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Ross gained 147 yards in 16 carries for L.A. Baptist (2-5, 2-0 in 
league) and quarterback Robin Woo completed seven of 12 passes for 56 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Maranatha (3-3, 1-1) was forced to play without three starters as quarterback 
Nathan Covey, running back Jordan McMahon and defensive back Darryl Ussery and 
were involved in a automobile accident heading to the game after the team 
dinner. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell-Jeff 39, St. Genevieve 13 -- The Guards controlled the line of scrimmage, 
rushing 29 times for 256 yards and four touchdowns, dropping the visiting 
Valiants to 0-7 and 0-4 in Santa Fe League play. 
</P>
<P>
 The Guards (4-3, 3-1) scored on runs of eight, 13, 16 and two yards. Danny 
Hughes rushed eight times for 72 yards, and sophomore Tommy Gales had 49 yards 
on five carries, including a two-yard score. 
</P>
<P>
 David Matekel had touchdown receptions of 19 and 24 yards to lead the Guards. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Richard Szeptycki completed five of seven passes for 94 yards and 
two touchdowns to Matekel. A Szeptycki pass was picked off by Eric Tapia, who 
returned it 85 yards for a touchdown to make the score 26-13 in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Tapia also had four catches for 49 yards, including a 15-yard touchdown that 
gave the Valiants their only lead of the evening, 7-6, in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Vince Pisano completed six of 16 pass attempts for 79 yards for the Valiants. 
</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick 34, Western Christian 7 -- Mario Qualls did a little of everything 
and led the visiting Mustangs (5-2, 1-1) to an Alpha League victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Qualls had two pass receptions for 34 yards, rushed 13 times for 78 yards -- 
including touchdown runs of 46 and four yards -- and returned a punt 62 yards 
for his third score to fuel a 28-0 Kilpatrick lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustang defense limited the Lancers (2-5, 0-2) to 93 yards of total 
offense, forcing 6 turnovers. Wardell Joe, Cleo Cloman, Edward Lyde and Levell 
Ziegler all had interceptions for Kilpatrick. Cloman's and Lyde's interceptions 
were returned for touchdowns. 
</P>
