<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; SANTA ANA WINS ITS FIRST OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An interception by Carlos Rodriguez halted a potential game-winning drive by 
winless Tustin as host Santa Ana earned its first victory of the season in a 
9-3 Golden West League game Saturday night at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a big victory for us because it puts us back in the hunt for the 
playoffs," Santa Ana Coach Bob Hinman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez picked off a pass by Tustin quarterback Kevin Timone at the Santa 
Ana 29 with 2 minutes 27 seconds remaining to secure the victory for the Saints 
(1-6, 1-1). Tustin (0-7, 0-2) has lost 13 consecutive games. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Esparza's one-yard touchdown run with 11:15 left in the second quarter 
was enough for Santa Ana, which also scored a safety late in the fourth 
quarter.  
</P>
<P>
 Tustin, which blew scoring opportunities with four turnovers, took the early 
lead on a 26-yard field goal by Adam Thomasson on its opening drive.  
</P>
<P>
 The Tillers compiled 172 yards in offense to 212 for Santa Ana, which won 
despite being assessed 105 yards in penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 In an Arrowhead League game: 
</P>
<P>
 Anza Hamilton 25, Southern California Christian 0 -- Rocky Meyers ran for 164 
yards and four touchdowns to lead host Hamilton. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamilton (5-1, 2-0) recorded its fifth shutout of the season, holding the 
Flames to 28 yards total offense, including three yards on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
 The Flames (1-6, 0-2) held the Bobcats in check the first quarter, holding 
Meyers to 24 yards rushing. 
</P>
<P>
 But Meyers put the Bobcats on the scoreboard with 5:43 left in the second 
quarter, scoring on a two-yard run for a 6-0 lead. The touchdown capped a 
14-play, 69-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Meyers' second touchdown came on a four-yard run with 34 seconds left in the 
half. The score, which gave Hamilton a 12-0 halftime lead, was set up by a 
51-yard completion from quarterback Erik Contreras to Donny Bonga. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bobcats wasted no time scoring in the third quarter. Meyers scored on a 
15-yard run on Hamilton's opening drive with 7:44 left in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamilton stifled the Flames' offense, giving up one first down the last two 
quarters. 
</P>
<P>
 Meyers capped the scoring late in the fourth quarter, with a one-yard 
touchdown run with 3:13 left to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Contreras completed five of nine passes for 104 yards and running back Nick 
Rueda added 76 yards in eight carries for the Bobcats. 
</P>
<P>
 Laramy Lumley ran for 31 yards in 11 carries to lead the Flames' offense. 
</P>
<P>
 In eight-man games: 
</P>
<P>
 In the Delphic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Liberty Christian 47, Huntington Beach Claremont 0 -- David Trujillo rushed 
for 98 yards and a touchdown in 12 carries, and Paul Malcolm carried only five 
times, but scored three touchdowns for host Liberty Christian (5-1-1, 1-0-1). 
Liberty Christian led, 27-0, at halftime. 
</P>
