<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; MATER DEI UPSETS NO. 1 MILLIKAN IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roberta Gehlke had 26 kills as eighth-ranked Mater Dei upset Long Beach 
Millikan, ranked No. 1 in Division II, 15-9, 15-8, 11-15, 6-15, 15-9, in a 
nonleague volleyball match Saturday at Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
 Laurie Layton had 62 assists for the Monarchs (10-4). Millikan is 12-5. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Ram Challenge: 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 3, Stockton St. Mary's 2 -- Misty May had 36 kills and Melissa 
Schutz had 25 to lead the Sailors, California's top-ranked team to a 12-15, 
15-12, 15-13, 12-15, 15-7 victory over San Jose St. Mary's, the third-ranked 
team, in a rematch of last year's State semifinal match, which was also won by 
Newport Harbor in five games. 
</P>
<P>
 In an earlier match, Newport Harbor defeated San Jose Archbishop Mitty, the 
ninth-ranked team in the state, 15-7, 15-4, 15-9. In that match, May had 17 
kills and Schutz had 11. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Marlborough tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza captures title -- Esperanza, the ninth-ranked team in Division I, 
captured the championship of the Marlborough tournament with a 16-14 victory 
over Los Angeles Notre Dame Academy, the fourth-ranked team in Division II. The 
Aztecs defeated Arcadia, 15-8, in a semifinal game. 
</P>
<P>
 In the championship of the Estancia Classic water polo tournament: 
</P>
