 BETTER READING: The country's magazine publishers begin four days of fun and 
idea-trading at the Ritz-Carlton hotel in Dana Point today. And they have no 
shortage of household names to help them do it. . . . Monday it's entertainment 
mogul Barry Diller. Tuesday's lineup includes O.J. Simpson lawyer Johnnie 
Cochran -- pending court matters -- plus author and former columnist Anna 
Quindlen. . . . And Wednesday's grand finale: Warren Beatty, scheduled to talk 
about Hollywood and the media. 
