<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN KILLED AND 3 INJURED IN COLLISION ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old woman was killed Saturday morning on the Golden State Freeway 
when the driver of the car she was riding in lost control of the vehicle and 
collided with a truck, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 May Wong of Fresno was with three other family members heading south on the 
Golden State Freeway when the 9:12 accident occurred north of Vista Del Lago 
Road, said Officer Kerri Hawkins of the California Highway Patrol.The car 
caromed off the center railing and hit the truck broadside. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of Wong's relatives, whose names were not released, were treated and 
released from Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital, a hospital spokeswoman 
said. The third relative was listed in serious condition. 
</P>
<P>
 No one in the truck was injured, Hawkins said. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash closed off two lanes of the freeway for about 3 1/2 hours. 
</P>
