<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 DIE IN SANTA ANA DRIVE-BY SHOOTINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two gang-related drive-by shootings that occurred about an hour apart Friday 
night left two men dead, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The first shooting took place around 9:30 p.m. in the 1700 block of West 
McFadden Avenue.Jose Luis Silva, 18, was riding his bicycle across the street 
when a vehicle approached him, said Sgt. Eric Vedborg. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was shot several times," Vedborg said. "One of the bullets struck him in 
the head and he died at the scene." 
</P>
<P>
 Vedborg said Silva, a resident of Santa Ana, was a known gang member. 
</P>
<P>
 The second shooting occurred at 10:40 p.m. in the 1900 block of West 17th 
Street. Freddy Fernandez, 23, of Santa Ana was hit by several bullets fired 
from a car. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Fernandez) was walking down the street when a vehicle drove alongside of him 
and stopped. A passenger leaned out and fired a bunch of shots," Vedborg said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fernandez was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange where he later died. 
</P>
<P>
 Police would release few details about the shootings on Saturday because they 
are still under investigation by gang investigators. No arrests have been made, 
Vedborg said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
