COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WILSHIRE; REDEVELOPMENT PLAN FOCUS OF MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Wilshire Center/Koreatown Community Advisory Committee will review and 
discuss a draft redevelopment plan for the area in a public meeting Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 This and the next few meetings will focus on land use, said Cooke Sunoo, 
Community Redevelopment Agency project manager, who added that community 
involvement is therefore important. 
</P>
<P>
 The redevelopment area, which was established after the 1992 riots to promote 
the rebuilding and economic revitalization of the Wilshire Center/Koreatown 
area, is bounded roughly by 5th Street to the north, 12th Street to the south, 
Hoover Street to the east and Western Avenue and Wilton Place to the west. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will begin at 3:30 p.m. in Room 311 of the Southwestern University 
School of Law, 675 S. Westmoreland Ave. Information: (213) 977-2633. 
</P>
