<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAME OF THE WEEK; FRANKLIN RINGS UP WILSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Franklin Coach Armando Gonzalez's motivation to beat Wilson was to capture 
sole possession of first place in the Northern Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 "The conference is the most important thing," Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Panther running back Octavio Verduzco had another inspiration: "I'm a senior 
and I didn't want to lose the bell." 
</P>
<P>
 The bell, a symbol of the Franklin-Wilson rivalry that is passed on to the 
annual winner, will remain at Franklin another year thanks to Verduzco's three 
rushing touchdowns in the Panthers' 48-26 win Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Verduzco rushed for 114 yards in 20 carries and scored on six-yard run and 
twice on three-yard runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Panther quarterback Jeff Deno and wideout Johnnie Sanders connected twice on 
scoring passes of 9 and 72 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders finished the game with eight catches for 168 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson wide receiver Buster Bradley, who had 121 all-purpose yards, scored on 
a four-yard run to bring the Mules within 34-26 with 6:24 remaining in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But Franklin scored 14 fourth-quarter points, including a 37-yard fumble 
return by defensive lineman Sergio Villasenor. 
</P>
<P>
 Records: Franklin 6-1; Wilson 5-2 
</P>
<P>
 Next week: Lincoln at Franklin; Belmont at Wilson 
</P>
