</P>
<P>
 Lincoln 22, Belmont 10--Defensive end Javier Pedroza's 39-yard interception 
return late in the fourth quarter helped give Lincoln a win in a Northern 
Conference game Friday at Lincoln. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing 10-7 after three sluggish quarters, Lincoln rallied when Jose Guevara 
scored on a 24-yard run up the middle to put the Tigers ahead for good, 16-10, 
after a two-point conversion. 
</P>
<P>
 Withe less than two minutes remaining, Belmont's final drive to tie the score 
ended when George Rodriguez threw a screen pass that bounced out of Fabian 
Villa's hands. Pedroza caught the loose ball and raced to the end zone. 
</P>
